FBIS3-19770 "drweu055__a94015" FBIS-WEU-94-055-A Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 ANNEX France Poll Gauges Popularity of Politicians, Parties BR1703112694 Paris PARIS MATCH in French 17 Mar 94 pp 78-79--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1703112694 Paris PARIS MATCH Language: French Article Type:BFN ["PARIS MATCH"-B.V.A. Opinion Poll: "Balladur Down Two Points: End of His Period of Grace, for 58 Percent of the French, He Lulls the People. Juppe Enjoys Highest Confidence Rating: Up Nine Points"] [Text] The latest PARIS MATCH-B.V.A. opinion poll discloses that the period of grace which the prime minister was enjoying, is over. Edouard Balladur's popularity dropped by 2 percent, although he is still supported by 53 percent of the people. Our survey reveals that 58 percent of the French think that he has a tendency to lull the French to sleep; 51 percent think he does not speak the truth. An absolute majority of those interviewed think that the prime minister has the style of a head of state, but there is also a negative side to this: 51 percent state that he thinks too much about the presidential election. Francois Mitterrand sees his popularity ratings rise by 3 percent, tilting the balance between positive and negative opinions into the positive region again. The big winner in this confidence poll is [Foreign Minister] Alain Juppe, whose rating soars by 9 percent. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |What is your opinion about Francois Mitterrand as president of the Republic? | |(February figures given in parenthesis) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Good |47 percent (44 percent) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Bad |46 percent (48 percent) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Do not know |7 percent (8 percent) | -------------------------------------------------------------------------