rs |comparison Feb 94 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Extreme Left |3 |3 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Communist Party (PC) |7 |8 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Socialist Party (PS)/Mov-|21 |21 | |ement for Rallyingthe Le-| | | |ft (MRG) | | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Generation Ecology |8 |7 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Greens |5 |5 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |UDF |16 |14 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |RPR |28 |30 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |National Front (FN) |12 |12 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |(19 percent of persons registered did not express their voting intention) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- This survey was conducted on a sample representative of the French population aged 18 years and over. The question referring to legislative election voting intentions was asked to 2,948 persons between 15 and 18 February and between 1 and 4 March 1994; the other questions were out to 973 persons between 1 and 4 March. Voting intentions are calculated on the basis of the number of persons registered for the elections. Sampling was done according to the quota method: sex; age; occupation of family head; and region and area (city, rural...). Results should be interpreted taking into account the usual error margins related to any poll and the size of the sample. There error margins are: approximately one to two points for voting intentions; approximately two to three points for the overall results; approximately four to five points for the results referring to the large political families.
